conclusion: Analyze the velocity-time graph of the skydiver's vertical movement.
The graph shows velocity increasing from 0 to 20 m/s at 10 seconds, then decreasing to 0 m/s at 15 seconds.
Identify intervals on the graph: 0 to 10 seconds and 10 to 15 seconds.
Calculate distance fallen from 0 to 10 seconds: 20 m/s * 10 s = 200 m.
Calculate distance fallen from 10 to 15 seconds: 0 m/s * 5 s = 0 m.
Compare distance fallen during 10 to 15 seconds interval to 75 meters: 0 m is less than 75 m.
Conclude distance fallen during 10 to 15 seconds interval is less than 75 meters.
